FBIS3-18666 "drweu044_q_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-044 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Mar 1994 TURKEY Government Officials Comment on Deputies' Immunity Mentese Notes `Judicial' Move TA0503144894 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1410 GMT 5 Mar 94 TA0503144894 Ankara ANATOLIA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Diyarbakir, Mar 5 (A.A) -- Interior Minister Nahit Mentese said on Saturday [5 March] that coalition government was resolved to eradicate the outlawed separatist terrorist organization. Mentese visited Anadolu Ajansi office in southeastern Diyarbakir Province. During the visit he said lifting the immunity of the Democracy Party [DEP] deputies was a judicial thing. Mentese said the government did its utmost for the region, however that separatist terrorist organization tried to hamper the development activities. Recalling the DEP Deputy Leyla Zana's words that lifting the immunities would cause more bloodshed in the region, Mentese said DEP and the separatist terrorist PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan] organization were one inside the other.
